com.sap.cloud.sdk.s4hana.datamodel.odata.services

Interface InternalOrderService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultInternalOrderService

    public interface InternalOrderService

    This service enables you to display internal order master data to be consumed in SAP Fiori apps and on other user interfaces.

    Business Documentation

    Reference: SAP API Business Hub

    Details:

    OData Service:API_INTERNALORDER_SRV
    API Version:1
    Communication Scenario:SAP Business Objects Cloud for Planning Integration (SAP_COM_0087)
    Scope Items:oData Integration with SAP Business Objects Cloud for Planning (1YB)

    • Method Detail

      • getAllInternalOrder

        InternalOrderFluentHelper getAllInternalOrder()
        Fetch multiple InternalOrder entities.
        Returns:
        A fluent helper to fetch multiple InternalOrder entities. This fluent helper allows methods which modify the underlying query to be called before executing the query itself. To perform execution, call the execute method on the fluent helper object.

      • getInternalOrderByKey

        InternalOrderByKeyFluentHelper getInternalOrderByKey(String internalOrder)
        Fetch a single InternalOrder entity using key fields.
        Parameters:
        internalOrder - Key that uniquely identifies an order within a client.

        Constraints: Not nullable, Maximum length: 12

        Returns:
        A fluent helper to fetch a single InternalOrder entity using key fields. This fluent helper allows methods which modify the underlying query to be called before executing the query itself. To perform execution, call the execute method on the fluent helper object.
